<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev, Qian Discuss `North Korean Nuclear Problem' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2901013594 Seoul YONHAP in English 0117 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2901013594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, Jan. 29 (YONHAP) -- China and Russia 
shared the opinion that it is vital for both South and North 
Korea not to have nuclear weapons in order to maintain peace and 
stability in the Korean peninsula, Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev says. 
  Kozyrev, who is on a visit to China from Wednesday, held a 
press conference on Friday in Beijing before leaving for 
Shenzhen and said that the North Korean nuclear problem was 
discussed during his talks with Chinese counterpart Qian Qichen. 
  He and Qian confirmed again their countries' opposition to 
the possession of nuclear weapons both by North and South Korea, 
he said. 
  Kozyrev said they are watching the situation on the Korean 
peninsula and that the principle of nuclear nonproliferation 
should be maintained for world peace and stability. 
  He said Russia and China should help solve the North Korean 
nuclear crisis. 
  There is the least possibility right now of war breaking out 
in the Asia-Pacific region since the Second World War, he said, 
but there still are chances of disputes among nations in the 
area. 
  He added that the positions of Russia and China on North 
Korea are very similar. 
  Kozyrev also said that he discussed with Qian ways to 
strengthen friendly and economic cooperation and to promote 
bilateral relations. 
  He hinted that he has discussed with Qian on ways of 
military 
cooperation between their two nations, but did not elaborate. 

</TEXT>

