<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Taiwan Official Reportedly Keen on Flights to China </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK3101101694 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 1014 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK3101101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, 26 Jan (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE)--Ku 
Chen-fu, chairman of Taiwan's Straits Exchange Foundation, 
responded to the issue of direct flights to fixed destinations 
on both sides of the strait, a issue which has recently drawn 
widespread attention in Taiwan; he said that the Taiwan 
authorities must have a policy on the issue, and must not avoid 
talking about it. Whereas the Hong Kong issue is also an urgent 
one, and the government should all the more derive a policy as 
soon as possible, and inform industrial and commercial circles 
at an early date so that they can make preparations. 
  Ku Chen-fu pointed out that based on the future economic 
policy of Taiwan, establishing an Asia-Pacific operation center 
and a special free trade zone is now a fixed direction; on this 
premise, the issue of direct flights between both sides of the 
strait cannot be always avoided, and preliminary planning should 
be done. He also said that the issue of direct flights between 
the two sides of the strait is not merely an economic issue, but 
should be considered together with planning for Hong Kong and an 
Asia-Pacific operations base. 
  In addition, regarding the Hong Kong issue, Ku Chen-fu said 
that Hong Kong is currently the cite of entrepot trade between 
Taiwan and the mainland, and that due to the importance of Hong 
Kong's position, Taiwan's future policy toward Hong Kong, as 
well as other relevant measures, are very important matters, and 
industrial and commercial circles must be allowed to understand 
them two or three years ahead of promulgation so they can make 
preparations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

