<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Taiwan's Mainland Investment Said To Exceed $25 Billion </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK3101141294 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in English 1345 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK3101141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, January 31 (CNS)--"The Taiwan Mainland 
Affairs Council of the Executive Yuan" said that Taiwan capital 
invested in the mainland was estimated to be between US$25 
billion and US$30 billion as of late last year. 
  A report by this Taiwan group pointed out that such a vast 
amount of capital was projected to have flowed into the mainland 
by the end last year in spite of a previous estimate by the 
council that Mainland-bound investment was expected to be 
US$19.4 billion as of November last year. 
  As for trade across the straits involving Hong Kong for this 
year, the report said that following a sharp devaluation of the 
renminbi early this year and the continuous opening of the 
Taiwan market to mainland raw materials as well as a relaxation 
of restrictions on mainland imports, a change in the pattern of 
trade between Taiwan and Hong Kong this year was expected, that 
is, a great rise in imports and a slow down of growth in 
exports. Products exported from Taiwan to the mainland will 
increase in volume rather than decline. 
  As for the investment sector, the report said that Hong Kong 
ranked fourth in terms of Taiwan investment abroad but Hong Kong 
investment in Taiwan and in the mainland showed a growing gap. 
Investment made by the territory in the mainland in 1992 was 200 
times that made in Taiwan during the same period while Taiwan 
became the second greatest investor in the mainland. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

