<F P=100> Latin America &amp; Caribbean </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC To Increase Links in Biology, Medicine With Cuba </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3101132394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1227 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3101132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 31 (XINHUA) -- China and Cuba will 
strengthen their cooperation in medical equipment, medical and 
biological products. 
  This was learned here today from the first Sino-Cuban 
Conference on Medical and Biological Sciences, at which a trade 
fair was also held on medical and biological products and 
equipment. 
  A spokesman for the conference said that "gratifying 
results" 
had been achieved in cooperation in the field of science and 
technology between the two countries. 
  He said that Cuba was good at medical and biological 
technology, which enjoys a superior position in governmental 
development schemes. 
  Sino-Cuban cooperation has excellent prospects in this 
field, 
the spokesman said. 
  The meeting was attended by a ten-member Cuban delegation 
and 
50 experts and enterprise managers from China. 
  It has been decided that the second fair and conference in 
this field will be held in Havana, the Cuban capital, at the end 
of this year. 

</TEXT>

