<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong People's Congress Adopts Six Local Laws </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0102095094 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in Chinese 1147 GMT 
18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0102095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Zhang Chuanxi (1728 0278 3556): "Guangdong </F>
Provincial People's Congress Standing Committee Adopts Six Local 
Laws and Regulations"] 
  [Text] Guangzhou, 18 Jan (ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE)--The Eighth 
Guangdong Provincial People's Congress Standing Committee met 
today and adopted six local laws and ordinances, including the 
"Properties Auction Regulations of Guangdong Province," the 
first of its kind ever introduced in the province. 
  The other five laws and ordinances adopted at the meeting 
are: "Regulations of Guangdong Province Governing Operation of 
Non-Government-Run Science and Technology Enterprises," 
"Regulations of Guangdong Province Governing Operation of 
Singing Lounges, Ballrooms, Cabarets, and Other Entertainment 
Establishments," "Ordinance of Guangdong Province for Protection 
of Enterprise Employees' Rights and Interests," "Regulations of 
Guangdong Province Governing Assignment of Real Properties in 
Urban Areas," and "Regulations of Guangdong Province on Job 
Arrangements for Personnel Discharged From Prisons and 
Reform-Through-Labor Camps." 
  The "Regulations of Guangdong Province Governing Operation 
of 
Non-Government-Run Science and Technology Enterprises" expressly 
provide that intellectual property rights can be converted into 
registered capital at a price based on legal assessment, but the 
proportion of capital invested as such shall not be higher than 
30 percent of the total registered capital. 
  The "Ordinance of Guangdong Province for Protection of 
Enterprise Employees' Rigths and Interests" reiterates the rule 
that no enterprise shall force workers to work overtime beyond 
the limit of working hours. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

