<H3> <TI>   Correction to Item on Old Guard, Political Influence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2701014594 </F>
<F P=103> HK2701014594 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  The following correction pertains to the item headlined 
"Old Guard Said To Maintain Political Influence," published in 
the Political &amp; Social section of the 13 January China DAILY 
REPORT, pages 22-24: 
  Page 22, second column, fourth paragraph of item, seventh 
sentence, make read: ...Deng Xiaoping and Chen Yun be 
maintained. However.... (correcting name to Chen Yun) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

