<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian Implements New Tax Legislation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2801033694 Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2801033694 </F>
<F P=104>  Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday, leaders at all levels throughout the 
province, almost 10,000 taxation cadres, as well as some 
officers and men in armed forces units and police corps 
stationed in Fujian, took to the streets to propagate the new 
Tax Law. This is the most extensive tax law propagation 
activity in Fujian since the founding of the PRC. 
  Recently the State Taxation Administration decided to 
conduct 
a month-long nationwide taxation propagation activity from 23 
January to 23 February. This activity had previously been 
scheduled for April this year. They also decided that 23 
January would be the first day of enforcement for the new Tax 
Law throughout the country. 
  Giving up their holidays yesterday, all taxation cadres set 
up more than 1,000 propagation centers throughout the province 
and also went to factories, mines, and enterprises, thus 
starting the month- long province-wide taxation propagation 
activity. 
  Wang Jianshuang, a member of the provincial party 
committee's 
Standing Committee and vice governor, took part in the 
propagation activity held in the [word indistinct] center in 
Fuzhou City. 

</TEXT>

