<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Trains Brokers for `Cultural Undertakings' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3101161094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1509 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3101161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, January 31 (XINHUA) -- China's first 
educational institute for training brokers engaged in cultural 
undertakings was set up today in this China's largest metropolis. 
  The training center will aim to ensure that brokers are 
qualified for cultural undertakings concerning literature, art, 
publishing, relics, tourism, the transfer of intellectual 
rights, video and audio products and fashion shows. 
  In its first term, the center will open two classes on 
training brokers dealing with transactions of cultural relics 
and arts and crafts. 
  The center is sponsored by the Shanghai Jiaotong University, 
the Shanghai Cultural Bureau and the Shanghai Administration for 
Industry and Commerce. 

</TEXT>

