<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guizhou Governor Solicits Deputies' Opinions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0102095294 Guiyang Guizhou People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0102095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Guiyang Guizhou People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday afternoon Governor Chen Shineng, other 
provincial leading comrades, and people in charge of the 
relevant departments took part in the discussions of various 
delegations to solicit their opinions and suggestions on 
government work. To make the People's Congress session more 
successful, the secretariat of the session had collected the 
delegation's opinions and demands in advance. Prior to their 
visit, these provincial leading comrades had summoned people in 
charge of the relevant departments to a meeting to clarify that 
they should carefully listen to the deputies' opinions and 
factually answer their questions. 
  Governor Chen Shineng listened to the opinions and demands 
of 
the delegation of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference. Three members of the delegation raised suggestions 
on highway construction, railway construction, grain and cotton 
production, animal husbandry development, assisting the poor, 
and combating corruption for a clean administration. 
  Governor Chen Shineng said that he would seriously consider 
their suggestions. People in charge of the relevant departments 
also factually answered their questions. 
  Vice Governor Mo Shiren went to Liupanshui's delegation to 
solicit their opinions. Members of the delegation requested 
listing Liupanshi City as an open city in the hinterland. Mo 
Shiren and comrades in charge of the relevant department 
answered their questions. 
  Vice Governors Hu Xiansheng, Zhang Yuqin, and Yao Jiyuan 
respectively went to the delegations of Tongren, Qiannan, and 
Zunyi to solicit their opinions. 

</TEXT>

