<H3> <TI>   Hebei Secretary Urges Frugality in Spring Festival </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0102053994 Shijiazhuang Hebei People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0102053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Shijiazhuang Hebei People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 29 January, Cheng Weigao, secretary of the 
provincial party committee, heard reports made by the provincial 
discipline inspection commission and the provincial departments 
concerned on how to spend a frugal Spring Festival and 
consolidate achievements in the struggle against corruption. 
  After hearing the reports, Cheng Weigao again urged that the 
party and government organs at various levels and their leading 
cadres should be honest and thrifty in their spending during the 
Spring Festival and that the discipline inspection and 
supervisory organs at various levels should strengthen 
supervision and inspections. 
  Cheng Weigao stressed: The year 1994 is a year for package 
reform and breakthroughs in key areas. So long as the leading 
cadres at various levels maintain honesty and establish close 
contacts with the masses, the reform measures will be supported 
by the masses and reform progress smoothly. Party committees 
and governments at various levels should always regard the 
opposition to corruption and the maintenance of honesty as a 
political task and grasp it. At present, we should grasp the 
issue of honesty during the Spring Festival. Leading cadres at 
various levels should take the lead in being honest. As for 
localities, departments, and units where many serious problems 
emerge, their principal leading cadres should first be called to 
account. 

</TEXT>

