<H3> <TI>   Liaoning's Shenyang Notes Anti-Embezzlement Acts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0102070894 Shenyang Liaoning People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0102070894 </F>
<F P=104>  Shenyang Liaoning People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Shenyang city anti-embezzlement bureau 
sponsored a press briefing on 31 January to inform journalist 
circles on the work results scored by the two city levels of 
procuratorial organs in investigating and handling economic 
crime in 1993. These procuratorial organs in Shenyang accepted 
452 cases of embezzlement and bribes and placed 366 cases on 
file for investigation and prosecution. They investigated and 
handled 36 economic cases involving party and government organs, 
judicial departments, administrative departments, and law 
enforcement departments. 
  (Ma Shiheng), former leader of the armed police brigade 
under 
the Shenyang city public security bureau, was arrested according 
to law on charges of embezzlement for accepting the largest 
amount of money ever in the processing of administrative 
accounts during his tenure. 
  On file for investigation and prosecution were cases 
involving (Chen Shijie), director of the drug policy and 
administration section under the provincial public health 
department, and (Liu Shangqian), cadre at the section level of 
the provincial public health department, for taking advantage of 
their power on numerous occasions to approve new drugs and new 
factories in exchange for huge bribes by pharmaceutical 
factories and sale centers. Both were arrested. 

</TEXT>

