<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   INTERFAX Cited on Georgian Defense Minister's Resignation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0202014594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0124 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0202014594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, February 1 (XINHUA) -- Georgian Defense 
Minister Gen. Karkarashvili announced his resignation today 
without giving any explanation for his decision. 
  The news center of the Georgian Defense Ministry had 
confirmed the resignation, but made no comment on the news, 
INTERFAX reported. 
  Meanwhile, President Eduard Shevardnadze's news office 
remained silent about the resignation. 
  Karkarashvili, a veteran of the Afghan war, became defense 
minister in 1993. He had asked for resignation twice before, 
but his request was rejected by Shevardnadze. 
  The minister had been scheduled to meet his Russian 
counterpart Pavel Grachev in Tbilisi on Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
